Place the meat into a bowl along with all the ingredients except the cheese and olive oil, and mix well to combine.Divide into two and form into patties.Place a piece of cheese in the centre of each burger and draw the meat over to cover.Reform to make a patty.Heat a griddle pan until very hot and drizzle with a little olive oil.Place the burger on the griddle and cook for 3-4 minutes on each side.Remove and serve in the ciabatta roll with some salad leaves.